<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Palantir (PLTR)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Palantir Technologies Inc. — using FY2025 actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026 · Data: FY2025 10-K</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">{roundedIV !== null && !isNaN(roundedIV) ? `$${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}` : "N/A"}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({roundedIV !== null && !isNaN(roundedIV) ? marginOfSafety : "N/A"}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {roundedIV !== null && !isNaN(roundedIV) ? verdictText : "Unavailable"}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fetchedRevenue[0] !== null ? `$${(fetchedRevenue[0] / 1000).toFixed(2)}B` : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY2025 Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fcf2025 !== null ? `$${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(2)}B` : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fetchedEPS[0] !== null ? `$${fetchedEPS[0].toFixed(2)}` : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{opMargin[0] !== null ? `${opMargin[0].toFixed(1)}%` : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{netCash !== null && !isNaN(netCash) ? `$${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : "N/A"}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Palantir generated <strong>$2.1 billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. This is operating cash flow ($2.13B) minus capital expenditures ($33.8M). Palantir's incredibly low capex model is a key driver of its high free cash flow conversion.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>25% per year</strong> for 5 years. Palantir's revenue grew over 56% in FY2025, largely driven by US Commercial and AIP adoption. While 56% is unsustainable long-term, 25% assumes Palantir maintains robust hypergrowth as AI spending scales.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>4.0% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). 4.0% represents GDP growth plus an aggressive tech moat premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>9%</strong> — our required rate of return. With a 10Y Treasury of 4.18%, this implies a lower risk premium, justified by Palantir's massive cash pile, zero structural debt, and highly sticky government contracts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash ($6.95B) = Equity Value. Divide by diluted shares outstanding (2.56B) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">25%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Palantir saw 56% revenue growth in FY2025, but assuming >50% growth for five years is extremely risky. We peg FCF growth at 25%, assuming high AIP adoption in commercial offsets slowing government growth, while low capex lets cash flow drop straight to the bottom line.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">9%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury is 4.18%. Palantir has essentially zero debt and massive net cash. It operates as a critical infrastructure layer for the US military and allied governments, making cash flows highly resilient. A 9% discount rate is appropriate for this lower-risk structural profile.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">4.0%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We add 1.0% for Palantir's unique position as an "OS for the modern enterprise and military." 4.0% is very aggressive for a perpetual growth rate, assuming Palantir remains a dominant tech layer indefinitely.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

